                <p class="intro"><strong>Exam technique for WCE/WCA MCQ scenarios</strong>: Read each scenario carefully and identify the specific claims principle being tested before reading the four options. The distractors in WCE/WCA scenarios typically apply the correct principle to the wrong facts, or substitute a UK-specific regulatory rule (FOS referral, FSCS protection, ICOBS 8) for the correct non-UK answer. Eliminate any option that references FCA, ICOBS, Consumer Duty, FOS, or FSCS as the operative rule — these are wrong answers in WCE/WCA. Focus on what the claims handler must do under the universal principle or the applicable local regulatory context described in the scenario.</p>

